<!-- WHY FLOOR GROUT GETS SO DIRTY -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">Why Floor Grout Gets So Dirty</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">Floor grout wears faster than any other grout in your home. Here's why it ends up looking so bad &mdash; even when you clean regularly.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">directions_walk</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Foot Traffic Grinds Dirt In</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Every footstep pushes dirt, dust, and grit into the grout lines. Over months and years, this grinds staining deep into the porous surface where no mop can reach it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">opacity</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Cement Grout Absorbs Everything</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Standard cement grout is porous &mdash; like a sponge. It soaks up spills, dirty mop water, soap residue, and anything else that touches it. Once absorbed, the staining is trapped inside the grout itself.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">cleaning_services</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Cleaning Doesn't Penetrate Deep Enough</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Most household cleaners only work on the surface. The staining you can see has soaked millimetres into the grout. Scrubbing removes the top layer, but the discolouration underneath stays put.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-3xl text-error mb-3 block" aria-hidden="true">vertical_align_bottom</span>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Grout Sits Lower Than Tiles</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">Grout lines are recessed below the tile surface, creating tiny channels where dirt, water, and debris naturally collect and settle. It's the lowest point on your floor &mdash; everything ends up there.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- CLEANING VS REGROUTING -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-surface-container-low">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">Cleaning vs Regrouting</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">Not every dirty floor needs a full regrout. Here's an honest breakdown of when cleaning is enough &mdash; and when replacement is the only fix that lasts.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-4xl">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border-2 border-surface-container">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary" aria-hidden="true">cleaning_services</span> Professional Deep Clean + Seal</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">If your grout is structurally sound &mdash; no cracks, no crumbling, no soft spots &mdash; and the staining is mostly on the surface, a professional deep clean followed by a quality sealer may be all you need. This is a legitimate option and we'll recommend it when it's appropriate.</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-outline font-medium uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Best for:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-secondary">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Surface-level staining only</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Grout is intact and firmly bonded</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Grout is less than 8-10 years old</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> No visible cracks or gaps</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-primary/[0.03] rounded-xl p-8 border-2 border-primary ring-1 ring-primary/10">
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary" style="font-variation-settings:'FILL' 1;" aria-hidden="true">check_circle</span> Full Floor Regrouting</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">If your grout is deeply discoloured right through, cracked, crumbling, or soft to the touch, no amount of cleaning will fix it. The grout itself is damaged or permanently stained. Replacement with fresh material is the only lasting solution.</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-outline font-medium uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Necessary when:</p>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-secondary">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Deep staining that won't lift with cleaning</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Cracked, crumbling, or missing grout</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Grout is soft, powdery, or flaking</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Previous cleaning attempts have failed</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary text-base flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">check</span> Grout is 15+ years old and worn out</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary mt-6 max-w-3xl">Send us photos and we'll give you an honest assessment. If cleaning is enough, we'll tell you &mdash; we'd rather give the right advice than sell work that isn't needed.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW FLOOR REGROUTING WORKS -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">How Floor Regrouting Works</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">A systematic process that removes every trace of old grout and replaces it with fresh, properly bonded material. We protect all surrounding furniture and fixtures throughout.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">1</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Assess All Floor Grout Lines</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">We inspect every grout line across the floor for staining depth, cracks, soft spots, and adhesion. This determines whether a full regrout is needed or if specific areas can be addressed. We also check for any loose tiles.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">2</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Remove Old Grout</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Using oscillating multi-tools fitted with diamond blades, we cut out all the old grout back to the tile edges. This exposes clean tile surfaces for proper adhesion of the new material. Dust is contained and extracted as we go.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">3</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Clean Joints Thoroughly</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">All joints are vacuumed and wiped to remove every trace of dust, debris, and old grout residue. Clean joints are essential &mdash; any contamination left behind will weaken the bond of the new grout.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">4</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Apply Fresh Grout</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">New grout is packed firmly into every joint. We use premium polymer-modified cement grout for most floors, or professional-grade waterproof epoxy grout for high-traffic areas, laundries, and commercial spaces. Colour matched to your choice.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">5</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Seal for Stain Protection</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Cement grout is sealed with a penetrating sealer that fills the pores and creates a stain-resistant barrier. This is what stops your new grout from getting dirty again quickly. Epoxy grout skips this step &mdash; it's already stain-proof.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">6</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Clean &amp; Inspect</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">All tile surfaces are cleaned of any grout haze or residue. We inspect every joint for consistency, coverage, and finish. Furniture protection is removed and the area is left clean and ready for use after curing.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-secondary mt-8 max-w-3xl"><strong>Note:</strong> Floor regrouting requires careful protection of skirting boards, cabinetry, and any fixtures that can't be moved. We cover and mask everything before work begins.</p>
    </div>
</section>

