<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white" id="faqs">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4 text-center">Floor Regrouting FAQs</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary text-center mb-10">Common questions about dirty floor grout and professional regrouting in Sydney.</p>

        <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Why is my floor grout so dirty?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Floor grout cops more punishment than any other grout in your home. Foot traffic grinds dirt, dust, and grime into the joints every day. Because cement grout is porous, it absorbs stains from spills, cleaning products, and general wear. The grout lines sit lower than the tile surface, so dirt naturally settles into them. Over time, even regular mopping can't reach deep enough to pull the staining out.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Can you just clean my floor grout instead of replacing it?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Sometimes, yes. If the staining is only surface-level and the grout is still structurally sound &mdash; no cracks, no crumbling &mdash; then a professional deep clean and seal may be all you need. We'll always be honest about this. But if the grout is deeply stained right through, cracked, or falling apart, cleaning won't fix it. Replacement is the only lasting solution in that case.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How long does floor regrouting take?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Most bathroom floor regrouting jobs are completed in a single day. Larger areas like kitchens or laundries may take a little longer depending on the floor size and tile layout. The floor is ready for light foot traffic 24 hours after completion to allow the new grout to cure.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Do I need to move furniture before you start?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">We ask that any freestanding furniture, mats, and loose items are moved off the floor beforehand. For fixed items like toilets and vanities, we work carefully around them and protect all fixtures and surfaces during the job. We'll let you know exactly what needs to be moved when we provide your quote.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Can you match the existing grout colour?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Yes. Grout comes in a wide range of colours and we can match or closely complement your existing tiles. Many customers choose a fresh, lighter colour to brighten up the floor &mdash; or a darker shade that hides future dirt better. We'll help you choose the best option based on your tiles and preferences.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">Does epoxy grout work on floors?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Absolutely &mdash; floors are actually where epoxy grout performs best. Epoxy is stain-proof, waterproof, and extremely hard-wearing, making it ideal for high-traffic bathroom floors, laundries, kitchens, and commercial spaces. It never needs sealing and won't discolour over time. It costs more upfront but saves money long-term because it doesn't need ongoing maintenance. <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/services/epoxy-grout-upgrade-sydney/' ) ); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium">Learn more about epoxy grout</a>.</p></div></div>

            <div class="faq-item border border-surface-container rounded-xl bg-surface-container-low"><button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-5 text-left" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm pr-4">How do I get a quote for floor regrouting?</h3><span class="material-symbols-outlined faq-chevron text-primary" aria-hidden="true">expand_more</span></button><div class="faq-answer px-5"><p class="text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed pb-5">Send us 3-4 photos of your floor grout through our <a href="<?php echo esc_url( home_url( '/contact/' ) ); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium">contact page</a> and we'll have a fixed-price quote back to you within hours. No call-out fee, no obligation. You can also call us directly on <a href="tel:<?php echo timeless_phone_link(); ?>" class="text-primary underline font-medium"><?php echo timeless_phone(); ?></a>.</p></div></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

